## Hints for Future Agents
- If you ever need iterator-level offset again, prefer the fetch_func approach
  already used by make_calls_iterator -- do NOT reintroduce the param; the old
  _get_one/_get_slice offset handling disagreed on the limit boundary.
- Public offset coverage lives in tests/trace/test_weave_client.py
  (test_get_calls_len ~L575, test_get_calls_limit_offset,
  test_get_calls_page_size_with_offset). Run with -k offset / -k get_calls.

## Codebase Discoveries
- get_calls(offset=N) => offset_override baked into effective_offset in
  fetch_func; the PaginatedIterator sees a stream already starting at N, so
  calls[0] is logical row N. The iterator never needed its own offset.

